Package com.att.research.xacml.std.datatypes

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IDateTime<T>
    IDateTime is the minimal interface an object needs to support in order to be used in XACML functions that expect a Date, DateTime, or Time.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Base64Binary
    Base64Binary provides utilities for converting the XACML base64Binary data type to and from String values.
    DataTypeAnyURI
    DataTypeAnyURI extends DataTypeBase for the XACML anyURI data type.
    DataTypeBase<T>
    DataTypeBase provides common implementation components of the DataType interface that is used by the specific instance implementations.
    DataTypeBase64Binary
    DataTypeBase64Binary extends DataTypeBase for the XACML base64Binary data type.
    DataTypeBoolean
    DataTypeBoolean extends DataTypeBase with conversions to the java Boolean type.
    DataTypeDate
    DataTypeDate extends DataTypeBase to implement the XACML Date type with a java Date representation.
    DataTypeDateTime
    DataTypeDateTime extends DataTypeBase for the XACML DateTime type.
    DataTypeDayTimeDuration
    DataTypeDayTimeDuration extends DataTypeBase to implement the XACML dayTimeDuration data type.
    DataTypeDNSName
    DataTypeRFC2396DomainName extends DataTypeBase to implement the XACML RFC2396 domainName data type.
    DataTypeDouble
    DataTypeDouble implements conversion to the XACML Double data type.
    DataTypeHexBinary
    DataTypeHexBinary extends DataTypeBase to implement the XACML hexBinary data type.
    DataTypeInteger
    DataTypeInteger extends DataTypeBase to implement the XACML integer type.
    DataTypeIpAddress
    DataTypeIpAddress extends com.att.research.xacml.common.datatypes.DatatypeBase to implement the XACML ipAddress data type.
    DataTypeRFC822Name
    DataTypeRFC822Name extends {@link com.att.research.xacml.common.datatypes.DataTypeBase> for the XACML rfc822Name data type.
    DataTypes
    DataTypes provides constant instances of the built-in DataType implementation classes.
    DataTypeSemanticStringBase<T extends SemanticString>  
    DataTypeString
    DataTypeString extends DataTypeBase to represent XACML 3.0 Strings as java Strings.
    DataTypeTime
    DataTypeTime extends DataTypeBase to implement the XACML Time data time mapping to a ISO8601Time java object.
    DataTypeX500Name
    DataTypeX500Name extends DataTypeBase to implement the XACML x500Name data type.
    DataTypeXPathExpression
    DataTypeXPathExpression extends DataTypeBase to implement the XACML xpathExpression data type.
    DataTypeYearMonthDuration
    DataTypeYearMonthDuration extends DataTypeBase to implement the XACML yearMonthDuration data type.
    ExtendedNamespaceContext
    ExtendedNamespaceContext allows holders of NamespaceContext to iterate through all elements within the Namespace, including the default.
    HexBinary
    HexBinary provides utilities for converting the XACML hexBinary data type to and from String values.
    IPAddress
    IPAddress represents either an IPv4 or IPv6 network address with optional (IPv4)masks or (IPv6)prefixes and port range components.
    IPv4Address
    IPV4Address extends IPAddress for IPv4 addresses.
    IPv6Address
    IPV4Address extends IPAddress for IPv4 addresses.
    ISO8601Date
    ISO8601Date is a representation of an ISO8601 format date without a time component.
    ISO8601DateTime
    ISO8601Datetime is a combination of an ISO8601Date and a ISO8601Time with a common ISO8601TimeZone.
    ISO8601Duration
    ISO8601Duration implements the ISO8601 duration data type with parsers from strings and to strings.
    ISO8601Time
    ISO8601Time represents a time of day with an optional timezone indication using ISO8601 standard representations for time, ordering, and operations.
    ISO8601TimeZone
    ISO8601TimeZone represents an ISO8601 TimeZone specification.
    NodeNamespaceContext
    NodeNamespaceContext extends NamespaceContext by delegating to the owning Document.
    ParseUtils
    ParseUtils provides a number of static methods that are useful in parsing String objects into other java data types.
    ParseUtils.ParseValue<T>  
    PortRange
    PortRange represents the optional range of port values for an IPAddress.
    RFC2396DomainName
    RFC2396DomainName represents a host name from the RFC2396 specification.
    RFC822Name
    RFC822Name represents an RFC 822 name consisting of a local part and a domain part.
    StringNamespaceContext
    StringNamespaceContext extends NamespaceContext by keeping the Namespace definitions as Strings.
    XPathDayTimeDuration
    XPathDayTimeDuration extends ISO8601Duration to restrict values to day and time components only, and then provides for ordering based on canonical duration in fractional seconds.
    XPathExpressionWrapper
    XPathExpressionWrapper implements the XPathExpression interface to wrap another XPathExpression and keep the path expression that was used to create it.
    XPathYearMonthDuration
    XPathYearMonthDuration extends ISO8601Duration to implement the XPath yearMonthDuration data type.
